						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the kitchen in the Bhaktavatsalēśvara temple, right of entrance.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vijaya-Bhūpatrirāya Śaka 1331 = 1409 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is engraved in continuation of No. 66 above.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of 32 cows and a bull for a perpetual lamp to the temple of Tirukkaḻukkuṉṟamuḍaiya-nayiṉār by Aḻagiya-Tiruchchiṟṟambalamuḍaiyār of Neṟkuḷam.</p>						

